## Material Selection

The selected alloy was:

### Aluminum 7475-T7651

- Young’s Modulus: 10 × 10⁶ psi  
- Poisson Ratio: 0.29  
- Ultimate Strength: ~65 ksi  
- Fracture Toughness (K<sub>IC</sub>): ~46 ksi√in  

This material provided favorable fatigue resistance and toughness while enabling a narrower reduced section for controlled strain amplification.

---

## Finite Element Analysis (ANSYS)

### Boundary Conditions

- Drive end fully constrained over the upper 0.40 in  
- Applied torsional loading equivalent to 600 in·lbf  

### FEM Results

