## Sensitivity Prediction (mV/V)

Using a half-bridge Wheatstone configuration, the estimated output was computed as:

<div style="background:#f6f8fa; padding:12px; border-radius:6px;">
V<sub>out</sub> / V<sub>in</sub> ≈ (Gauge Factor × 2 × Strain) / 4  
<br>Using GF ≈ 2.05 and ε ≈ 1.055 × 10⁻³  
</div>

### Final Sensitivity  
≥ 1.0 mV/V at 600 in·lbf  
This satisfies the project requirement.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

**Selected Gauge:** Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350  
**Type:** Linear foil strain gauge, 350 Ω, Gauge Factor ≈ 2.05  

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th>Gauge Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Grid Length</td><td>3.18 mm</td></tr>
<tr><td>Grid Width</td><td>1.57 mm</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pattern Type</td><td>Linear</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

This gauge was selected based on compatibility with the redesigned mounting surface and the predicted FEM strain distribution.

---

## Conclusion

The final torque-wrench configuration:

- Meets all structural, fatigue, and fracture safety criteria  
- Achieves more than double the baseline sensitivity  
- Produces well-defined strain fields for half-bridge instrumentation  
- Integrates CAD, materials engineering, strain-gauge application, and FEM validation into a unified design workflow  

---
